{
  "name": "SetVaultAccessPolicy",
  "description": "This operation configures an access policy for a vault and will overwrite an existing policy. To configure a vault access policy, send a PUT request to the <code>access-policy</code> subresource of the vault. An access policy is specific to a vault and is also called a vault subresource. You can set one access policy per vault and the policy can be up to 20 KB in size. For more information about vault access policies, see <a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/amazonglacier/latest/dev/vault-access-policy.html\">Amazon Glacier Access Control with Vault Access Policies</a>. ",
